      transliteration: "īśāvāsyam idaṁ sarvaṁ yat kiñca jagatyāṁ jagat\ntena tyaktena bhuñjīthā mā gṛdhaḥ kasya svid dhanam",
      translation: "All this — whatever moves in this moving world — is wrapped in the Lord. Enjoy it, therefore, through letting go. Do not covet: whose is wealth, anyway?",
